Power is the product of voltage and current and you have to have both to actually do useful things with electricity.  Voltage alone is just potential.  If there's no current flowing, it's possible to have a lot of voltage without really being able to do anything useful.  Batteries are rated as a product of current and time--Amp Hours (AH) or milli-Amp Hours (mAH).  That is, they are rated by how long they can produce a given current.  A 500mAH battery should be able produce 500 milliamps for an hour, or 250 milliamps for 2 hours.  The  voltage doesn't really change a lot over the life of the battery, but eventually, as it is drained, the amount of current it can put out goes down to nothing.
